So the Communication Agent and Feedback Agent have a clear separation of responsibilities:

* Communication Agent is responsible for orchestrating the conversation, logging inbound/outbound communications, and generating the notification draft.
* Feedback Agent is responsible for enriching the minimal input (claim_number and comment) by looking up claim details, determining the current stage, analyzing sentiment, calculating escalation risk, and updating the feedback-related tables. This design keeps the Communication Agent lightweight while centralizing sentiment and feedback logic in the Feedback Agent.
